A total of four teams have qualified for the knockout stages of the Champions League following Tuesdayâ€™s matches. They are: Barcelona, Juventus, Sevilla and Chelsea. Barca who were without talismanic captain, Lionel Messi, thrashed Dynamo Kiev 4-0 in Ukraine. Sergino Dest opened scoring in the second half, before Martin Braithwaite added a brace. Antoine Griezmann climbed off the bench to net the last goal. Juventus grabbed the second slot from Group, after they saw off Ferencvaros 2-1, with Alvaro Morata scoring a late winner. Sevilla and Chelsea both won 2-1 against Krasnodar and Rennes respectively.